snippet: The election of Tammy Baldwin as the country’s first openly gay senator this week came only six years after Wisconsin voted down a gay marriage initiative.
abstract: Election of Rep Tammy Baldwin, seven-term Democrat from Madison, Wis, makes her the country's first openly gay senator; hard-fought win is testament to unorthodox politics of a state known for its wide ideological swings and affirmation of her starkly progressive views.
lead_paragraph: The election of Tammy Baldwin as the country’s first openly gay senator this week came only six years after Wisconsin voted down a gay marriage initiative.

headline.seo: Fickle Wisconsin Sends Tammy Baldwin, Trusty Progressive, to Senate
